  "plot_summary": "[ASSET: right | GreatestSymbolInComics | width=30%] [HANG0] * This is the first month in Marvel's history where the upper‑left corner of the covers featured a small figure of the book's main character(s) -- the birth of the Marvel corner symbols.\n[BR]\n[BR] Legend has it that Steve Ditko came up with the idea, and when Stan Lee saw it, he immediately ordered it used across the entire line.&nbsp; A response to Paul Weinstein's letter in FF #18 confirms Ditko's role, and early fan reaction was overwhelmingly positive.\n[BR]\n[BR] A full‑page notice in [LINK:1963:ASM_2_asm1|ASM #2] (also printed with [LINK:1963:FF_14|FF #14]) trumpets them as \"the greatest symbols in comics!\" -- each paired with the \"Marvel Comics Group\" box beside the 12 cover price.\n[BR]\n[BR] Interestingly, the rollout wasn't perfectly synchronized:&nbsp; several books in the February batch (including this month's <i>Journey Into Mystery</i>) missed the cutoff, suggesting some issues had already gone to press.&nbsp; That seems to be rectified by next month, with even the <i>non-</i>superhero output falling in line.\n\n[ASSET: right | SpecialAnnouncement | width=28%] [HANG0] * [LINK:1963:FF_14|FF #14]'s special announcement page addresses the many requests for letters pages in the anthology mags (that I affectionately call <i>Journey Into Strange Tales of Suspense to Astonish</i>).&nbsp; Marvel admits they don't have the bandwidth to produce them, so the FF letters page will become the \"melting pot\" for all titles except <i>Spider‑Man </i>(which already has its own).&nbsp; Expect letters about Thor, Ant‑Man, Human Torch, and Iron Man to show up in FF for the time being.\n\n[ASSET: right | SgtFuryComingSoon | width=25%] [HANG0] * [LINK:1963:FF_14|FF #14] also announces the upcoming debut of a brand‑new title:\n[BR] <i>Sgt. Fury and His Howling Commandos</i>.",
